The paper deals with the problem of building a data collection tree in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI). The problem formulation involves optimizing the network lifetime, which is a common objective in distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and proposes an algorithm to solve it, which falls under the category of computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DC). The use of variable transmission power levels and accounting for sensor energy consumption also suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm using Jain's fairness index, which is a metric commonly used in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT).
